The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 25 August is 2,919 (337.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 21 August, there were 50 new confirmed cases (5.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 14 August, there were 32 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 56% (18 extra cases).
